            As regards the question on which the noble Lord, Lord Mackay of Ardbrecknish, was trying to press&#x2014;the possibility of the need for regional rather than national advice in England&#x2014;it would be a matter not necessarily of regulation, which is how he phrased his question, but perhaps a difference in advice. For example, in a major dairying area of England, advice
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_53gc' title='Col. 53GC &mdash; HL Deb 12 October 1999 vol 605 c53GC' name='column_53gc' href='#column_53gc' rel='bookmark'>53GC</a>
